title: Ampatuyoc (Ayacucho)
text: Ampatuyoc (possibly from <a href="Quechua%20language">Quechua</a> "hamp'atu" frog, "-yuq" a <a href="suffix">suffix</a> to indicate ownership, "the one with a frog (or frogs)") is a mountain in the <a href="Andes">Andes</a> of <a href="Peru">Peru</a>, about high. It is located in the <a href="Ayacucho%20Region">Ayacucho Region</a>, <a href="V%C3%ADctor%20Fajardo%20Province">Víctor Fajardo Province</a>, <a href="Sarhua%20District">Sarhua District</a>.
